---

<section class="services" id="services">
  <div class="eyebrow">Services</div>
  <div class="accent-bar"></div>
  <h2>What I Can Do For You</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">
    Engagements range from architecture reviews and strategic advisory to hands-on delivery.
    Every engagement starts with understanding the business problem, not the technology solution.
  </p>

  <div class="cards">

    <div class="card featured">
      <div class="card-left">
        <div class="card-label"><span class="dot"></span>01</div>
        <h3>AI &amp; Agentic Systems</h3>
        <p>
          The opportunity isn't chatbots. It's systems that act — that reason across tools,
          data sources, and workflows on behalf of the business. I build AI-native applications
          that go beyond wrappers: semantic evaluation engines, knowledge pipelines, edge inference
          systems, and agentic workflows that integrate with the systems you already run.
          If your AI strategy is "we added a chatbot to the website," we have work to do.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-right">
        <p class="card-aside">
          This is where language, computation, and business converge. Large language models
          aren't just a new tool — they're the first technology in decades that rewards
          the combination of linguistic fluency, engineering depth, and business judgment
          simultaneously. That intersection is where I work.
        </p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">LLM integration</span>
          <span class="tag">Agentic architecture</span>
          <span class="tag">MCP</span>
          <span class="tag">RAG pipelines</span>
          <span class="tag">ML inference</span>
          <span class="tag">SageMaker</span>
          <span class="tag">Edge AI</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-label"><span class="dot"></span>02</div>
      <h3>Cloud Architecture</h3>
      <p>
        I hold current AWS certifications in solutions architecture and machine learning,
        and I've designed multi-tier serverless systems, VPC architectures, and CI/CD pipelines
        as hands-on work — not just coursework. What I bring beyond the technical foundation
        is 25 years of knowing how technology decisions play out inside organizations: what gets
        funded, what gets maintained, and what quietly becomes someone else's problem in three years.
        I design with that perspective built in.
      </p>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">AWS</span>
        <span class="tag">Serverless</span>
        <span class="tag">VPC</span>
        <span class="tag">IAM</span>
        <span class="tag">IaC</span>
        <span class="tag">CI/CD</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-label"><span class="dot"></span>03</div>
      <h3>Enterprise Modernization</h3>
      <p>
        I've run the programs where the answer was "we need to rebuild this, the right way,
        without stopping the business." Legacy platform migration, application portfolio
        rationalization, large-scale modernization with real budgets and real consequences.
        The technical work is the easy part. The hard part is keeping the organization moving
        while the floor is being replaced beneath them.
      </p>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">Legacy migration</span>
        <span class="tag">Platform transformation</span>
        <span class="tag">SAFe</span>
        <span class="tag">Portfolio rationalization</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card wide">
      <div class="card-label"><span class="dot"></span>04</div>
      <h3>Technology Strategy &amp; Advisory</h3>
      <p>
        Sometimes the most valuable thing isn't someone to write the code — it's someone
        to tell you what to build, in what order, and why. I work with leadership teams to
        develop technology roadmaps, evaluate vendors, structure engineering organizations,
        and translate between what the business needs and what the technology team can
        realistically deliver.
      </p>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">Fractional CTO</span>
        <span class="tag">Roadmap development</span>
        <span class="tag">Vendor selection</span>
        <span class="tag">Team structure</span>
        <span class="tag">Budget planning</span>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .services {
    padding: 6rem 4rem;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .accent-bar {
    width: 48px;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--accent-dark);
    border-radius: 2px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 600px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .card {
    background: var(--surface-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2.25rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .card:hover { border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3); }

  .card.featured {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(37,99,235,0.12) 0%, var(--surface-card) 55%);
    border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .card.wide { grid-column: 1 / -1; }
  .card.wide p { max-width: 680px; }

  .card-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .dot {
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .featured .card-label::after {
    content: 'Priority Focus';
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    background: rgba(96,165,250,0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.3);
    color: var(--accent);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-soft);
  }

  .card-aside {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .tag {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
</style>
